<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>MEMORANDUM FROM THE NATURAL ENVIRONMENT RESEARCH COUNCIL IN RESPONSE TO THE INTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT COMMITTEE INQUIRY INTO DEMOCRACY AND DEVELOPMENT IN BURMA</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Natural</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Environment</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Research</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Council</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The Natural Environment Research Council (NERC) is one of the UK’s seven Research Councils.  It funds and carries out impartial scientific research in the sciences of the environment and trains the next generation of independent environmental scientists.  Details of NERC’s research centres and research programmes are available at</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">www.nerc.ac.uk</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NERC does not fund the socio-economic aspects of environmental issues; nor does it become involved in the politics of said i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ssues.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NERC is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> therefore</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> unable to offer signif</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">icant insight into this issue and our comments are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> from a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> scientific and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">environmental perspective</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> only</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">This response is based on input from NERC Swindon Office and the National Oceanography Centre (NOC).</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How NERC </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">could help DFID</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> and Burma:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Coastal regions of Burma (Myanmar) are vulnerable to storm surges, sea level rise and tsunami.  NOC has world-class expertise in sea level rise, storm surge modelling, and an understanding of coastal processes that could be available for DFID to offer Burma in a future capacity building or disaster mitigation programme.  A DFID-funded capacity building programme to increase local resilience would be a worthwhile contribution to development in Burma.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NOC could also bring international assistance to bear through its involvement in the World Meteorological Organisation Disaster Risk Reduction group on Coastal Hazards</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  Dr Kevin Horsburgh, Head of Marine Physics and Ocean Climate (MPOC) Research Group at NOC, co-chairs the World Meteorological Organisation (WMO) Disaster Risk Reduction Focal Points of Technical Commissions and Programmes (DRR FP TC-TP) whose mission is to deliver the WMO Disaster Risk Reduction Work Plan (2012-2015).  This plan aims to facilitate better alignment of the activities of WMO constituent bodies and global operational network (of which Myanmar is a member</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">) in the following:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Identify, prioritize, establish partnerships and service delivery agreements with national D</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">isaster </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">isk </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">eduction (DRR)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> user community engaged in various DRR activities such as risk analysis, Multi-Hazard Early Warning Systems (MHEWS), sectoral risk management, disaster risk financing and transfer (DRR users);</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Develop and deliver core and specialized products and services (e.g., data, forecasts, analysis, technical advices and a range of other value-added products and services) defined by the requirements of the “DRR users” for DRR decision support (e.g., hazard/risk analysis, multi-hazard EWS, sectoral risk management and disaster risk financing and risk transfer) in a cost-effective, systematic and sustainable manner;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Ensure that core operational capacities (e.g., observing networks, forecasting systems, telecommunication systems, data management systems, human resources, etc.) are built upon the principles of Quality Management Systems (QMS) to support product and service development and delivery;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Establish partnership agreements with other national technical agencies (e.g., hydrological services, ocean services, etc.) and with global and regional specialized centres (e.g. Global Producing Centres (GPC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">), Regional Specialized Meteorological Centres (RSMCs), Regional Climate Centres (RCC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">), Tsunami Watch Centres, etc.), with standard operating procedures;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Engage in regional and global efforts for development of risk information for large scale and trans-boundary hazards, through strengthened regional and global cooperation.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">NERC </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Research grants involving Burma:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NERC has </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">recently awarded </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a grant to study </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Coseismic deformation associated with the 11th November 2012 Shwebo earthquake, Myanmar</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> (see </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Annex A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  The results will be widely communicated so they may be used to inform development policy in Myanmar and other seismically active areas.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Annex A</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt; width:100.34%"><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"></td><td style="vertical-align:middle; width:77.74%"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="vertical-align:middle; width:21.94%"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"></td><td style="vertical-align:middle; width:77.74%"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">NERC Reference : </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">NE/K016474/1</span></p></td><td style="vertical-align:middle; width:21.94%"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><a href="javascript:self.history.back()"><img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABAAAAAQCAYAAAAf8/9hAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAABdSURBVDhPY/iPDzx/jlcaJMmAU8Xatf//nztHpgEgzdnZZBoA00yWAciaSTYAXTNJBmDTTLQBuDTTzwBQTFPkBVhSoSgQcRlCVkqkKCGhu4QsFyAbQpEBIIOIyM4Av5S86qVj2+cAAAAASUVORK5CYII=" width="16" height="16" alt="Description: Back to previous page" /><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">Back to previous page</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p></td></tr><tr style="height:20.25pt"><td style="background-color:#e7e8ff; padding:0.75pt; vertical-align:middle; width:0.84%"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td colspan="2" style="background-color:#e7e8ff; padding:0.75pt; vertical-align:middle"><